---
description: Communication standards for agent responses
alwaysApply: true
---

When communicating with the user:

- Use code citation blocks to reference existing code: ```startLine:endLine:filepath format. Code citations are strictly better than describing code in prose.
- Code citation fences (the opening ```) MUST be on their own line, never prefixed by list markers or other text on the same line.
- Inside fenced code blocks and inline backticked text, content is shown literally: do not use HTML character references.
- In code citations, skip large irrelevant chunks using `...` or pseudocode comments.
- In non-citation code blocks meant for copy-pasting, write full commands with no omissions.
- Users prefer markdown links for ease of navigation when referencing web content.
- Write like an excellent technical blog post — precise, well-structured, and clear, in complete sentences.
- Keep final responses proportional to task complexity.
- Do not overuse bolding or backticks for decoration.
- Avoid engagement baiting at the end of responses.
